An elegie upon the much lamented death of the Right Honourable, the Lord Brooke.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
Printed by Robert Austin, and Andrew Coe, [London] : 1643.
Verse - "Weep not unthrifty mourners: why so fast". Place of publication from Wing. With engraved border. Annotation on Thomason copy: "March. 7.". Imperfect: copy stained and cropped with loss of print. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
